        <num>CCP 2341</num>
        <heading>2341.  Sale when installment not due</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2341.  Sale when installment not due
When the seizing creditor has a security interest, mortgage, lien, or privilege on the property seized, for a debt of which all the installments are not due, he may demand that the property be sold for the entire debt, on the same terms for the payment of unmatured installments as provided in the original contract.</p>
        </content>
